column1: On 3 January 2019, how many U.S. senators will be women?
column6: ['US Politics']
column11: In the current 115th United States Congress, 23 of 100 senators are women (ABC News). The number of women filing Senate candidacies ahead of the 2018 midterms could be record-setting (New Yorker, Center for American Women and Politics, Inside Elections). Confused? Check our FAQ or ask us for help.

column6: 115th Congress has adjourned.
Time.
Time.
No reason to think that Congress will not reconvene on January 3rd, especially with the continuing shutdown.
There has been no progress with the budget, so chances are higher that it won't be resolved by the third.

The only time a shutdown has occurred at this time of the year, from what I can find, was '95-96. They convened on time that year. Being that it is a sample size of one, I will average it with the 40% on time rate over the past 20 years.
If the shutdown is not resolved, I don't see how Congress doesn't start on January 3rd.
Ducey said Sinema will be sworn in first on Jan. 3, giving her not just the title of being the state’s senior senator but also the bragging rights of being Arizona’s first female senator.

Women in the U.S. Congress 2018 In 2018, 107 (78D, 29R) women hold seats in the United States Congress, comprising 20.0% of the 535 members; 23 women (23%) serve in the U.S. Senate , and 84 women (19.3%) serve in the U.S. House of Representatives .

To arrive at these numbers, I use 538's classic forecast numbers, but then manually increase the higher and lower tail probabilities to account for the fact that the chance for electing women are correlated between races.

Currently, there are 23 women serving in the U.S. Senate. This year, more women are running for elected office than ever before, which increases the chances that more women will be elected to the senate. In Arizona, for example, both the republican and democrat candidate for senate are women and are running to replace a man (Jeff Flake). This all suggests that its likely that the number of women senators will increase.
